(Psalm 73:28) . . . "But as for me, the drawing near to God is good for me. In the Sovereign Lord Jehovah I have placed my refuge, To declare all your works." They would have a close relationship with God. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/eb/Choose-a-Spouse-According-to-the-Bible-Step-2.jpg/v4-459px-Choose-a-Spouse-According-to-the-Bible-Step-2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/e/eb/Choose-a-Spouse-According-to-the-Bible-Step-2.jpg/v4-759px-Choose-a-Spouse-According-to-the-Bible-Step-2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
